page.title: 18St. Mary's Church, Farcet
page.content: We went to visit the church. The vicar showed us round. He told us that the nave of the church was{800 years}old but many parts have been added. The church that we see today was finished in{1900.}We went up into the belfry and saw one bell that was{three {hundred}years old. We looked up into the roof and saw{imps}and{monkeys carved into the roof. One of the stained glass windows had a picture of Mary and{Joseph}on it. We looked at different parts of the church. The date{1614}was carved on the pulpit. Near the big wooden door was a porch with seats all around.
